  "description": "GKE Node Auto-Provisioning (NAP) \u2014 the GA, Google-native Karpenter equivalent. Visualizes the elastic, Spot, scale-to-zero capacity that the ci-spot Custom ComputeClass provisions for bursty CI agents, alongside the static platform pool. Node membership (Spot / ci-spot) is read from the node TAINTS via kube-state-metrics (kube_node_info / kube_node_spec_taint), which scripts/03-observability.sh keeps even in the lean/free Grafana Cloud profile (a tiny node-inventory allow-list), so this board works in all observability modes.",
  "editable": true,
  "fiscalYearStartMonth": 0,
  "graphTooltip": 1,
  "id": null,
  "liveNow": false,
  "panels": [
    {
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 12,
        "w": 24,
        "x": 0,
        "y": 0
      },
      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "code": {
          "language": "plaintext",
          "showLineNumbers": false,
          "showMiniMap": false
        },
        "content": "## Node Auto-Provisioning (NAP) \u2014 Elastic Spot CI nodes\n\nGKE **Node Auto-Provisioning** creates and destroys Spot VM node pools on demand \u2014 the Google-native equivalent of Karpenter. The `ci-spot` **Custom ComputeClass** drives it: Spot-first VM families (`c3 \u203a n2 \u203a c2 \u203a e2`) with on-demand fallback, targeting a **scale-to-zero** cost profile between builds.\n\n| Pool | Lifecycle | Healthy state |\n|---|---|---|\n| \ud83d\udfe0 **Spot (NAP)** | Auto-provisioned when CI pods are pending \u00b7 deleted \u22485 min after idle | `0` at rest \u00b7 rises during builds |\n| \ud83d\udfe3 **ci-spot ComputeClass** | Subset of Spot tagged with the `ci-spot` class | Should equal Spot count |\n| \ud83d\udfe2 **Static** (`jenkins-2026-pool`) | Always-on: Jenkins \u00b7 ArgoCD \u00b7 CNPG \u00b7 observability | Must stay **\u2265 1** \u00b7 if `0` \u2192 incident |\n\n**Reading the elasticity chart** \u2014 a healthy build cycle looks like **`0 \u2192 N \u2192 0`**\n\n\ud83d\udfe0 Spot climbs when the scheduler sees pending CI-agent pods (\u22482 min provisioning), peaks during the build, then drops as NAP consolidates idle nodes (\u22485 min after the last pod exits). \ud83d\udfe2 Static must stay flat \u2014 any dip is a platform incident. The dashed **Total** line always equals Static + Spot.\n\n---\n**No Spot data?** `kube_node_spec_taint` only emits while a Spot node is live. \u2460 Trigger a build \u00b7 \u2461 Verify `kube-state-metrics` is running \u00b7 \u2462 Run `gcloud container node-pools list` to confirm NAP pools",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "13.2.0-28226228576",
      "targets": [],
      "title": "",
      "type": "text"
    },
